      "\n     - `A = toNat(e.Y + e.X) ≡ toNat(e.Y) + toNat(e.X) = Y + X mod p`.\n     - Similarly for the other congruences.\n\nBut again, to do this in Lean, we need to actually have `pn.Y_plus_X = e.Y + e.X`, etc., which we don't know.\n\n**Alternative Approach**:\n   - Since we can't inspect Lean's implementation of `as_projective_niels`, we might instead need to take `pn := e.as_projective_niels.get!`, and then `A := toNat(pn.Y_plus_X)`, etc., and then just",
      "\n  have h₁ : e.asprojective_niels = ok e.asprojective_niels.unsafe := by\n    simp [e.asprojective_niels]\n  have h₂ : (Field51_as_Nat e.asprojective_niels.unsafe.Y_plus_X : ℕ) % p = (Field51_as_Nat e.Y + Field51_as_Nat e.X) % p := by\n    simp [ProjectiveNielsPoint]\n    <;> rfl\n  have h₃ : (Field51_as_Nat e.asprojective_niels.unsafe.Y_minus_X : ℕ) % p = (Field51_as_Nat e.Y - Field51_as_Nat e.X) % p := by\n    simp [ProjectiveNielsPoint]\n    <;> rfl\n  have h₄ : (Field51_as_Nat e.asprojective_niels.unsafe.Z : ℕ) % p = (Field51_as_Nat e.Z : ℕ) % p := by\n    simp [ProjectiveNielsPoint]\n    <;> rfl\n  have h₅ : (Field51_as_Nat e.asprojective_niels.unsafe.T2d : ℕ) % p = (Field51_as_Nat e.T * Field51_as_Nat backend.serial.u64.constants.EDWARDS_D2) % p := by\n    simp [ProjectiveNielsPoint]\n    <;> rfl\n  simp_all [h₁]\n  <;>\n  (try norm_num)\n  <;>\n  (try ring_nf)\n  <;>\n  (try aesop)",
      "\n  have h₂ : (e.to_proj_niels : ProjectiveNielsPoint) = e.to_proj_niels := rfl\n  refine' ⟨e.to_proj_niels, _⟩\n  constructor\n  · -- Prove that as_projective_niels e = ok pn\n    exact h₁\n  · -- Prove the congruences for A, B, Z', C\n    dsimp only\n    have h₃ : (Field51_as_Nat (e.to_proj_niels.Y_plus_X)) % p = ((Field51_as_Nat e.Y) + (Field51_as_Nat e.X)) % p := by\n      simp [to_proj_niels, getY_plus_X]\n      <;>\n      (try decide) <;>\n      (try ring_nf) <;>\n      (try simp_all [Field51_as_Nat, p, Nat.ModEq]) <;>\n      (try norm_num) <;>\n      (try\n        {\n          rfl\n        })\n    have h₄ : (Field51_as_Nat (e.to_proj_niels.Y_minus_X)) % p = ((Field51_as_Nat e.Y) - (Field51_as_Nat e.X)) % p := by\n      simp [to_proj_niels, getY_minus_X]\n      <;>\n      (try decide) <;>\n      (try ring_nf) <;>\n      (try simp_all [Field51_as_Nat, p, Nat.ModEq]) <;>\n      (try norm_num) <;>\n      (try\n        {\n          rfl\n        })\n    have h₅ : (Field51_as_Nat (e.to_proj_niels.Z)) % p = (Field51_as_Nat e.Z) % p := by\n      simp [to_proj_niels, getZ]\n      <;>\n      (try decide) <;>\n      (try ring_nf) <;>\n      (try simp_all [Field51_as_Nat, p, Nat.ModEq]) <;>\n      (try norm_num) <;>\n      (try\n        {\n          rfl\n        })\n    have h₆ : (Field51_as_Nat (e.to_proj_niels.T2d)) % p = ((Field51_as_Nat e.T) * (Field51_as_Nat backend.serial.u64.constants.EDWARDS_D2)) % p := by\n      simp [to_proj_niels, getT2d]\n      <;>\n      (try decide) <;>\n      (try ring_nf) <;>\n      (try simp_all [Field51_as_Nat, p, Nat.ModEq]) <;>\n      (try norm_num) <;>\n      (try\n        {\n          rfl\n        })\n    exact ⟨h₃, h₄, h₅, h₆⟩",
      "\n  refine' ⟨e.to_projective_niels, by simp [h₁], _⟩\n  dsimp\n  <;>\n  (try decide) <;>\n  (try\n    {\n      simp [ProjectiveNielsPoint.mk.injEq]\n      <;>\n      norm_num [p]\n      <;>\n      rfl\n    }) <;>\n  (try\n    {\n      rfl\n    }) <;>\n  (try\n    {\n      simp_all [Field51_as_Nat]\n      <;>\n      norm_num [p]\n      <;>\n      rfl\n    })\n  <;>\n  (try\n    {\n      simp_all [Field51_as_Nat]\n      <;>\n      norm_num [p]\n      <;>\n      rfl\n    })\n  <;>\n  (try\n    {\n      simp_all [Field51_as_Nat]\n      <;>\n      norm_num [p]\n      <;>\n      rfl\n    })\n  <;>\n  (try\n    {\n      simp_all [Field51_as_Nat]\n      <;>\n      norm_num [p]\n      <;>\n      rfl\n    })",
